==Loot==
Once a birdhouse is full, it can be collected for loot, which includes [[raw bird meat]], [[feather]]s, and the [[clockwork]] that was used to build the birdhouse.

Birdhouses will also give varying numbers of [[bird nest]]s, dependent on the tier of birdhouse and [[Hunter]] level.{{CiteNews|author=The Old School Team|url=https://secure.runescape.com/m=news/bird-nest-balancing-and-pvp-changes?oldschool=1|title=Bird Nest Balancing and PvP Changes|newsdate=22 November 2018|name=BirdNestBalancing}} Each birdhouse will give at most 1 seed nest, followed by 10 chances to get nests off the nest table. The nest table drops regular empty nests, ring nests, egg nests, and rarely also [[clue nest]]s.

In addition, wearing a [[strung rabbit foot]] will replace about 5% of the empty nest drops with ring nests or egg nests.{{CiteNews|author=The Old School Team|url=https://secure.runescape.com/m=news/collection-log-improvements-and-the-last-of-poll-74?oldschool=1|title=Collection Log Improvements and The Last of Poll 74|newsdate=7 April 2021}} This is different from the bird nest mechanic while [[Woodcutting]], which reduces the number of seed nests.

The seeds used do '''not''' affect amount of nests received.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1019209471015387138|date=17 July 2018|archiveurl=https://archive.is/YvWnh|archivedate=27 May 2020|quote=[Do the seeds you place in birdhouses have an effect on the amount of nests you get?] No.|name=ashseedstweet}} Disassembling a birdhouse does not have a Hunter level requirement, meaning boosts only need to be used when placing birdhouses and not when disassembling them.

Using regular birdhouses, the expected number of bird nests per run is 2.1408 at level 5 and 7.1408 at level 99.

